column5: Did a cottage run today for a peek after the big winds last week.  	Lots  of limbs down but thankfully no damage. The neighbour a few doors down had his suspended aluminum dock ripped off the hinges.  	Scugog and the bottom of Pigeon skimmed over.  Gannon Narrows and upper Pigeon wide open. No snow.
I was up in the Hanover area yesterday. The lake I looked at was fully iced over. Hit it with a sledge hammer...inch and a half of ice.
